WEBVTT

00:03.567 --> 00:05.801
Okay. See these three guys?

00:05.801 --> 00:07.000
They're the wise men.

00:07.000 --> 00:09.601
They were kings who came
and brought presents.

00:09.601 --> 00:10.968
Well, only not like GoBots.

00:10.968 --> 00:13.300
They brought gold
and frankincense

00:13.300 --> 00:14.767
and myrrh.

00:14.767 --> 00:16.901
What's myrrh?

00:16.901 --> 00:19.300
It's like, um...

00:19.300 --> 00:20.501
wine or something.

00:20.501 --> 00:21.767
It's a spice.

00:21.767 --> 00:23.868
What's Baby Jesus
gonna do with wine?

00:23.868 --> 00:26.334
Oh, yeah, but he's got
lots of uses for a spice.

00:27.901 --> 00:30.167
I think I like
the other crÃ¨che better.

00:30.167 --> 00:32.934
You know, the one where
Joseph looks like Elvis?

00:35.667 --> 00:39.167
Hey, what's this doing
in with the Christmas stuff?

00:39.167 --> 00:40.701
Isn't that Kirsten's?

00:40.701 --> 00:42.868
Yeah.

00:42.868 --> 00:44.934
And these are her books

00:44.934 --> 00:47.567
and her
Harry Belafonte CDs.

00:49.968 --> 00:51.734
All this stuff
is Kirsten's.

00:51.734 --> 00:53.234
Hey, put that away.

00:53.234 --> 00:56.067
The UPS guy's gonna be here
in, like, seven seconds.

00:56.067 --> 00:58.100
Why are you
sending her stuff away?

00:58.100 --> 00:59.467
'Cause it's hers,

00:59.467 --> 01:02.033
and it should be in Chicago
where she is and not here

01:02.033 --> 01:03.200
where she's not.

01:03.200 --> 01:04.200
[TAPE TEARS]

01:04.200 --> 01:05.634
Don't you think
maybe you should

01:05.634 --> 01:07.133
take your time with this,
Charlie?

01:07.133 --> 01:08.534
I mean, what's the rush?

01:08.534 --> 01:09.868
The rush is the UPS guy's

01:09.868 --> 01:11.567
gonna be pissed off
if he has to wait.

01:11.567 --> 01:14.267
Or even worse, he'll just leave
without getting all this.

01:14.267 --> 01:16.267
JULIA:
You know, maybe
what you should do

01:16.267 --> 01:19.834
instead of shoving her stuff
out the door is let yourself,

01:19.834 --> 01:21.067
I don't know,

01:21.067 --> 01:22.501
feel this.

01:22.501 --> 01:24.033
I mean, this is--

01:24.033 --> 01:25.934
This is--

01:25.934 --> 01:27.267
Sad.

01:27.267 --> 01:28.667
Yes, it is sad.
But you know what?

01:28.667 --> 01:30.567
It's also smart,

01:30.567 --> 01:32.834
'cause I'm never gonna
start over if I start every day

01:32.834 --> 01:35.033
taking my toothbrush
from her toothbrush holder

01:35.033 --> 01:37.834
and end every night
setting her alarm clock.

01:37.834 --> 01:39.667
[DOORBELL RINGS]

01:39.667 --> 01:40.934
Tell him to wait two minutes.

01:42.467 --> 01:44.667
I really think that maybe you're
doing this too fast.

01:44.667 --> 01:46.000
CHARLIE:
I'll tell you what.

01:46.000 --> 01:48.200
Throw away the most important
thing you've ever had,

01:48.200 --> 01:51.133
then we'll talk.
You'll have to wait two minutes.

01:51.133 --> 01:52.200
Grandpa?

01:52.200 --> 01:53.634
JAKE:
How's my little girl?

01:53.634 --> 01:55.067
CLAUDIA:
Great.

01:55.067 --> 01:56.701
Oh.

01:56.701 --> 01:58.067
Merry Christmas, kids.

01:58.067 --> 01:59.968
I-I got a lot of stuff here.

01:59.968 --> 02:02.467
So, uh, show me the way
to the tree.

02:02.467 --> 02:03.834
[GIGGLES]

02:03.834 --> 02:07.767
[THE BODEANS' "CLOSER TO FIVE"
PLAYING]

02:08.901 --> 02:11.667
 <i>* Everybody wants to live *</i>

02:11.667 --> 02:13.534
 <i>* Like they wanna live *</i>

02:13.534 --> 02:17.033
 <i>* And everybody wants to love *</i>

02:17.033 --> 02:18.601
 <i>* Like they wanna love *</i>

02:18.601 --> 02:22.567
 <i>* Everybody wants to be *</i>

02:22.567 --> 02:27.334
 <i>* Closer to free-ee-ee-ee *</i>

02:27.334 --> 02:30.334
 <i>* Closer to free *</i>

02:37.400 --> 02:38.901
JAKE:
What do you mean, no tree?

02:38.901 --> 02:41.067
JULIA:
We wanted to go get one
in Charlie's truck,

02:41.067 --> 02:43.701
but that would necessitate
Charlie actually being there.

02:43.701 --> 02:48.033
As you saw, he's pretty much
Mr. Disappearing Act these days.

02:48.033 --> 02:50.901
Where did that guy
run off to so fast anyway?

02:50.901 --> 02:52.200
CLAUDIA:
The restaurant.

02:52.200 --> 02:55.100
He pretty much spends
all of his time there now.

02:55.100 --> 02:57.400
Why? He's not having
business problems, is he?

02:58.667 --> 03:00.534
More like personal ones.

03:00.534 --> 03:02.033
He had a pretty rough fall.

03:02.033 --> 03:04.434
Kind of took the holiday
spirit out of him.

03:04.434 --> 03:06.300
Oh.

03:06.300 --> 03:08.000
Well, what about Bailey?

03:08.000 --> 03:09.834
Ha. I can't even remember

03:09.834 --> 03:11.334
the last time I saw Bailey.

03:11.334 --> 03:12.801
JULIA:
He's got his own place now.

03:12.801 --> 03:14.567
You know, college and all.
And, frankly,

03:14.567 --> 03:17.033
he's kind of
in a bad way too, so...

03:17.033 --> 03:19.968
So the guys are in a funk,

03:19.968 --> 03:23.467
and you two are just gonna give
up on Christmas. That's it, huh?

03:23.467 --> 03:25.968
Well, I mean, it's not like
we have much of a choice.

03:25.968 --> 03:28.567
Even with the few
decorations up,

03:28.567 --> 03:30.701
the house is still
really depressing 

03:30.701 --> 03:32.200
with everyone gone.

03:32.200 --> 03:33.968
Maybe we should just
bag the whole thing.

03:33.968 --> 03:35.968
Let the rest of the world
celebrate Christmas,

03:35.968 --> 03:37.534
and we'll just have Wednesday.

03:37.534 --> 03:39.133
JAKE:
Oh, no, nothing doing.

03:39.133 --> 03:41.567
I brought a lot of darn nice
Christmas gifts here.

03:41.567 --> 03:44.634
But first, they've gotta
sit under a Christmas tree.

03:44.634 --> 03:47.167
So come on, let's get our coats
and get going.

03:47.167 --> 03:49.734
You too, kiddo.
Where are we going?

03:49.734 --> 03:51.634
We're gonna march down
to that lot

03:51.634 --> 03:53.667
I saw at the base of the hill.

03:53.667 --> 03:56.200
We're gonna pick out the
finest-looking Christmas tree

03:56.200 --> 03:59.000
we can find, and then we're
gonna drag it back up the hill

03:59.000 --> 04:00.167
to the house.

04:06.901 --> 04:08.200
Callie?

04:08.200 --> 04:09.934
You still here?

04:12.501 --> 04:13.968
[MACHINE BEEPS]

04:13.968 --> 04:15.667
CALLIE [OVER MACHINE]:
 <i>Okay. I'm gone.</i>

04:15.667 --> 04:17.634
 <i>My checks for rent and phone</i>
 <i>are on the mantel.</i>

04:17.634 --> 04:19.200
 <i>Send them. Bye.</i>

04:19.200 --> 04:20.701
Yeah, lot of warmth there.

04:20.701 --> 04:23.033
SARAH:
 <i>Bailey, are you there?</i>

04:23.033 --> 04:26.234
 <i>I'm leaving for the airport,</i>
 <i>and I just thought...</i>

04:26.234 --> 04:29.234
 <i>I don't know that</i>
 <i>we should talk before I go.</i>

04:29.234 --> 04:30.901
 <i>Okay, maybe I'll try back.</i>
 <i>Bye.</i>

04:30.901 --> 04:31.934
[MACHINE BEEPS]

04:31.934 --> 04:33.067
CLAUDIA:
 <i>It's me.</i>

04:33.067 --> 04:35.100
 <i>When are you coming home? Call.</i>

04:35.100 --> 04:36.100
 <i>Bye.</i>

04:36.100 --> 04:37.367
[MACHINE BEEPS]

04:37.367 --> 04:39.067
SARAH:
 <i>Okay. Now we're really leaving,</i>

04:39.067 --> 04:41.701
 <i>I just thought I should</i>
 <i>wish you a Merry Christmas</i>

04:41.701 --> 04:43.234
 <i>and vice versa, but--</i>

04:43.234 --> 04:45.400
 <i>Okay. I'm-- I'm coming.</i>

04:45.400 --> 04:46.834
 <i>Okay. I gotta go.</i>

04:46.834 --> 04:48.033
 <i>Bye.</i>

04:48.033 --> 04:49.701
[MACHINE BEEPS]

04:49.701 --> 04:52.000
JULIA:
 <i>Bailey, there's some stuff</i>
 <i>going on over here,</i>

04:52.000 --> 04:53.501
 <i>and we</i>
 <i>could really use you around.</i>

04:53.501 --> 04:55.234
 <i>So call.</i>

04:55.234 --> 04:57.033
[MACHINE BEEPS]

04:57.033 --> 05:00.267
CLAUDIA: <i>Bailey, it's Claudia--</i>
JULIA: <i>I just called him.</i>

05:00.267 --> 05:01.901
CLAUDIA:
 <i>Oh.</i>

05:01.901 --> 05:03.868
 <i>Well, call already.</i>

05:03.868 --> 05:05.701
 <i>Bye.</i>

05:05.701 --> 05:07.567
[RINGS]

05:15.267 --> 05:16.934
[GRUNTING]

05:18.767 --> 05:20.567
Now, how's that?

05:20.567 --> 05:22.133
Mm. A little bit this way.

05:22.133 --> 05:23.267
[DOORBELL RINGS]

05:23.267 --> 05:24.701
I'll get it.

05:28.167 --> 05:29.767
STUART:
Merry Christmas.

05:31.033 --> 05:32.934
Stuart, what is this?

05:32.934 --> 05:34.334
I can't say.
You gotta open it.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.501
Carefully. It's fragile.

05:36.501 --> 05:39.501
You got this for me?
Yeah.

05:39.501 --> 05:41.601
I thought real hard
about what you'd like,

05:41.601 --> 05:44.000
and, well, let's just say
I think I did pretty well.

05:44.000 --> 05:45.400
[CAR HONKING]

05:45.400 --> 05:46.968
Oh, I-- I gotta go.

05:46.968 --> 05:50.133
I'm helping my mom
deliver latkes to our friends.

05:50.133 --> 05:52.167
Man, I wish I could stay
to see your expression

05:52.167 --> 05:53.567
when you open it.

05:57.567 --> 05:58.667
Wow.

05:58.667 --> 06:00.834
Someone's trying
to impress you.

06:00.834 --> 06:02.834
Impress me?

06:02.834 --> 06:04.067
Why?

06:05.667 --> 06:07.801
You--? You think
he bought me this because...?

06:07.801 --> 06:09.200
[LAUGHS]

06:09.200 --> 06:10.267
Because...?

06:10.267 --> 06:12.567
Stuart has got a crush.

06:12.567 --> 06:13.868
No.
Yeah.

06:13.868 --> 06:15.100
No, no, no, no, no.

06:15.100 --> 06:16.601
He can't. No.

06:16.601 --> 06:18.901
I-I don't want him to.
I-I don't like him like that.

06:18.901 --> 06:20.501
I barely like him not like that.

06:22.534 --> 06:24.033
I mean, what am I gonna do?

06:24.033 --> 06:25.868
Easy. Just make sure
the gift you give him

06:25.868 --> 06:27.434
tells him how you feel.

06:27.434 --> 06:29.968
I'm not gonna buy him a present.
He'll think I like him back.

06:29.968 --> 06:31.767
Not if it's
a totally impersonal,

06:31.767 --> 06:34.100
completely pro forma gift
that doesn't mean anything.

06:37.567 --> 06:40.300
Where do you learn this stuff?

06:40.300 --> 06:42.501
["DECK THE HALLS" PLAYING
OVER STEREO]

06:42.501 --> 06:44.767
Who do you have to know
to get a drink around here?

06:44.767 --> 06:46.400
Hey, Jake,

06:46.400 --> 06:47.400
what can I get for you?

06:47.400 --> 06:49.467
Oh, I'll have a beer.

06:51.767 --> 06:55.734
I figured this might be
my last chance to talk to you.

06:55.734 --> 06:59.834
You ran out of the house
so fast this morning.

06:59.834 --> 07:01.601
Yeah. It's, uh...

07:01.601 --> 07:03.200
It's crazy around here.
Heh.

07:03.200 --> 07:05.400
We're all involved
in this homeless shelter,

07:05.400 --> 07:07.167
and I just decided
to do a New Year's party

07:07.167 --> 07:09.100
for the first time ever.

07:09.100 --> 07:12.234
Well, it's nice to stay busy
when you got the blues.

07:14.534 --> 07:16.234
Claudia told me

07:16.234 --> 07:18.133
about what happened
with your girlfriend.

07:18.133 --> 07:19.634
I-I'm sorry about that.

07:21.167 --> 07:23.234
Your sisters

07:23.234 --> 07:26.901
miss having you
around the house, Charlie.

07:26.901 --> 07:28.000
They can handle it.

07:29.534 --> 07:31.434
Don't you think
you oughta head back there

07:31.434 --> 07:32.767
just for a while?

07:32.767 --> 07:36.567
Look, I-I know you're probably
trying to help here,

07:36.567 --> 07:38.267
but doing
this whole Christmas thing--

07:38.267 --> 07:41.200
It's just making me feel
kind of...

07:41.200 --> 07:42.534
stuck right now.

07:44.267 --> 07:46.367
So I oughta butt out, huh?

07:46.367 --> 07:48.334
Yes, please.

07:50.667 --> 07:52.968
I gotta-- I just-- I gotta
focus on new stuff now,

07:52.968 --> 07:56.067
get new interests, find new
places to put my energy.

07:56.067 --> 07:58.234
'Cause if I do that,
then I'll be able to start over,

07:58.234 --> 08:00.133
you know, and I won't spend
the rest of my life

08:00.133 --> 08:01.667
paying for one mistake.

08:03.534 --> 08:05.067
I mean, you know
how this is, right?

08:05.067 --> 08:07.734
You made a big mistake
and got past it.

08:07.734 --> 08:10.033
Oh, did I get past it?

08:10.033 --> 08:12.033
Yeah, in some ways,

08:12.033 --> 08:14.200
maybe I did.

08:14.200 --> 08:16.100
Yeah.

08:16.100 --> 08:18.567
But in other ways, no.

08:20.234 --> 08:23.801
Well, I'm sorry about that.

08:23.801 --> 08:25.734
That's not gonna happen to me.

08:28.467 --> 08:30.400
[PANTING, GRUNTING]

08:34.067 --> 08:36.000
RUSS:
Bailey.

08:36.000 --> 08:37.400
Oh, man.

08:37.400 --> 08:40.067
What are you doing?

08:40.067 --> 08:41.667
What does it look like?

08:41.667 --> 08:43.767
Like you're working out
at 7:00 at night

08:43.767 --> 08:45.200
in the middle of vacation.

08:45.200 --> 08:46.901
It's 7?

08:46.901 --> 08:48.701
No way.
Yeah.

08:48.701 --> 08:50.868
Why? How long
you been here?

08:50.868 --> 08:52.434
I don't know. Since 4.

08:52.434 --> 08:54.968
You know, most freshmen
are home right now,

08:54.968 --> 08:56.534
eating decent meals,

08:56.534 --> 08:58.334
getting a good night's sleep
for a change.

08:58.334 --> 08:59.667
Yeah?

08:59.667 --> 09:01.834
More power to 'em.

09:01.834 --> 09:04.334
You do have a place to go,
right? Like your family's?

09:04.334 --> 09:06.067
Yeah.

09:06.067 --> 09:08.367
I do. I'm just not going.

09:10.067 --> 09:11.868
So, what are you
gonna do for vacation?

09:11.868 --> 09:13.968
You're looking at it.

09:13.968 --> 09:16.300
At least it's good
for me, right?

09:16.300 --> 09:18.200
Actually, it's not.

09:18.200 --> 09:20.634
Students who don't step away
from this place now and then

09:20.634 --> 09:23.400
end up climbing clock towers
with high-powered rifles.

09:23.400 --> 09:26.033
Come on, get out of there.

09:29.067 --> 09:30.767
Why don't you
come to my place tomorrow?

09:30.767 --> 09:32.400
I'm gonna watch the game.

09:32.400 --> 09:34.033
I don't think so.

09:35.100 --> 09:37.467
Oh, that wasn't a request.

09:37.467 --> 09:39.133
Kickoff is at 2:00.

09:39.133 --> 09:40.834
I'll see you then, huh?

