What about this one, O?
 <i>The Night Before Christmas.</i>

09:52.634 --> 09:53.901
Ah.

09:53.901 --> 09:56.534
You want Grandpa
to read it to you, huh?

09:56.534 --> 09:59.000
Oh, is that what he wants?

09:59.000 --> 10:00.601
[CHUCKLES]

10:00.601 --> 10:02.234
Are you gonna read it?

10:02.234 --> 10:04.067
Well, I-I'll tell you what.

10:04.067 --> 10:05.901
I-- I gotta
be heading out.

10:05.901 --> 10:08.567
But, wait.
Wh-where you going?

10:08.567 --> 10:11.334
I'm going back to L.A.

10:11.334 --> 10:14.267
Ugh. Come on, I mean,
just don't leave.

10:14.267 --> 10:16.501
Yeah, you should stay.

10:16.501 --> 10:19.334
It's just starting
to feel like Christmas.

10:20.701 --> 10:22.067
Oh, it is, huh?

10:24.100 --> 10:26.067
Well, I guess I could

10:26.067 --> 10:27.601
stay a little.

10:27.601 --> 10:29.200
JULIA:
Of course you can.

10:29.200 --> 10:31.267
So take the book and read it
to Owen like he asked.

10:31.267 --> 10:33.267
Oh, now, wait a minute.
I don't know about that.

10:33.267 --> 10:35.601
No, no, see,
you can't say no. House rules.

10:35.601 --> 10:36.667
JAKE:
House rules?

10:36.667 --> 10:38.200
Then, uh, I guess I better.

10:38.200 --> 10:40.167
Yes, ahem, here we are.

10:41.634 --> 10:43.934
 <i>'Twas the night before</i>
 <i>Christmas</i>

10:43.934 --> 10:46.901
 <i>And all through the house</i>

10:46.901 --> 10:49.133
 <i>Not a creature was stirring</i>

10:49.133 --> 10:50.200
 <i>Not even a mouse.</i>

10:52.167 --> 10:54.033
 <i>The, uh, children</i>

10:54.033 --> 10:56.501
 <i>Were tucked</i>

10:56.501 --> 10:58.868
 <i>In their--</i>

10:58.868 --> 10:59.868
Nestled.
What?

10:59.868 --> 11:01.000
Beds?
Nestled.

11:01.000 --> 11:03.701
 <i>Nestled all tight</i>
 <i>In their beds,</i>

11:03.701 --> 11:05.667
 <i>While visions of sugarplums</i>

11:05.667 --> 11:07.267
 <i>Danced in their heads.</i>

11:09.133 --> 11:10.868
 <i>Uh, Mama in her kerchief,</i>

11:10.868 --> 11:12.400
 <i>And I in my cap...</i>

11:14.133 --> 11:16.234
Mama in her kerchief...

11:17.767 --> 11:19.267
and I in my cap...

11:20.033 --> 11:21.567
[MOUTHED SPEECH]

11:21.567 --> 11:23.167
Oh, no.
 <i>I rose from my bed</i>

11:24.501 --> 11:27.100
 <i>To see what was the matter.</i>

11:27.100 --> 11:29.267
You're on the wrong page.

11:29.267 --> 11:31.734
[***]

11:31.734 --> 11:33.901
Oh, oh.

11:33.901 --> 11:35.934
So I am.

11:35.934 --> 11:37.767
Yeah.

11:37.767 --> 11:39.167
So I am. Yeah.

12:06.767 --> 12:09.968
BAILEY:
See, these guys
know how to spend Christmas.

12:09.968 --> 12:11.601
Play a little ball,

12:11.601 --> 12:14.400
toss back a few beers,
call it a day.

12:14.400 --> 12:15.734
No caroling,

12:15.734 --> 12:17.267
no yule log.

12:17.267 --> 12:19.033
I'm impressed, Bailey.

12:19.033 --> 12:20.868
It usually takes people
35 years to work up

12:20.868 --> 12:23.067
a good holiday malaise.

12:23.067 --> 12:24.968
I've always been very
precocious.

12:24.968 --> 12:26.567
That's how I ended up
at State.

12:26.567 --> 12:27.868
Uh-huh.

12:30.100 --> 12:32.567
Hey, that's coming along.

12:32.567 --> 12:33.701
Yeah.

12:33.701 --> 12:36.167
Mandy has one
at her mom's in Connecticut

12:36.167 --> 12:37.767
we made before the divorce.

12:37.767 --> 12:38.968
I figured if she had one here,

12:38.968 --> 12:40.868
it would feel more like home,
you know?

12:40.868 --> 12:42.801
Hold that, will you?
Yeah.

12:42.801 --> 12:45.267
I just hope she
hasn't outgrown it.

12:45.267 --> 12:46.868
It's hard to know
when you only see her

12:46.868 --> 12:48.667
a few times a year.

12:48.667 --> 12:49.868
How old is she?

12:49.868 --> 12:51.033
Eleven.

12:51.033 --> 12:52.300
Yeah?

12:52.300 --> 12:54.033
I have a sister who's 13.

12:54.033 --> 12:55.567
Claudia.

12:55.567 --> 12:57.133
Does she still like
dollhouses?

12:57.133 --> 12:58.200
Nah, no way.

12:59.334 --> 13:02.567
Oh, but she only just
outgrew 'em.

13:02.567 --> 13:04.200
Really recently.

13:05.968 --> 13:07.701
Hm.

13:07.701 --> 13:09.267
It's crazy, you know.

13:09.267 --> 13:12.901
You feel like there's so much
riding on a stupid present.

13:14.367 --> 13:16.234
Th-that should be dry.

13:16.234 --> 13:17.701
What do you mean?

13:17.701 --> 13:19.000
Well, you know,

13:19.000 --> 13:21.400
what if she hates it?

13:21.400 --> 13:23.267
What if she looks at it

13:23.267 --> 13:25.000
and thinks I don't know her
at all?

13:26.868 --> 13:28.901
What if she's right?

13:31.667 --> 13:33.701
CLAUDIA:
He wasn't even
on the right page.

13:33.701 --> 13:35.934
He probably just figured
he knew the poem by heart,

13:35.934 --> 13:38.067
and then he forgot.

13:38.067 --> 13:39.300
Uh-uh.

13:39.300 --> 13:41.334
I mean, did you
see his face?

13:41.334 --> 13:43.467
He looked--
He looked scared.

13:43.467 --> 13:44.701
Maybe he was just confused.

13:44.701 --> 13:47.200
You know, that happens
to old people sometimes,

13:47.200 --> 13:49.634
but it's totally normal.

13:49.634 --> 13:50.868
So you really--?

13:50.868 --> 13:52.934
You really don't think
we should worry about it?

13:52.934 --> 13:54.634
No. No, not at all.

13:54.634 --> 13:57.000
But Stuart's gift
on the other hand...

13:57.000 --> 13:58.033
Hey.

13:59.267 --> 14:01.567
Perfect. Impersonal, yet fun,

14:01.567 --> 14:03.434
distant, yet good-humored.

14:03.434 --> 14:05.100
Cheap, yet cheap.

14:05.100 --> 14:07.033
Hey, do you wanna
send a message or don't you?

14:07.033 --> 14:08.434
I'm gonna have it
gift-wrapped.

14:08.434 --> 14:10.033
Paper and no bow.
Hee-hee!

14:11.400 --> 14:15.234
[SOFT JAZZ MUSIC
PLAYING OVER STEREO]

14:15.234 --> 14:16.334
Sorry about the overflow.

14:16.334 --> 14:18.200
Things get kind of crazy
around Christmas.

14:18.200 --> 14:20.567
It's okay, I just wish somebody
from the office told me.

14:20.567 --> 14:22.234
I would've made sure
there was enough.

14:22.234 --> 14:23.701
There is no one at the office.

14:23.701 --> 14:25.567
They cut our funding
for a secretary.

14:25.567 --> 14:28.234
Welcome to non-profit.
Ho-ho.

14:28.234 --> 14:30.167
[SCOFFS]

14:30.167 --> 14:31.634
What a world, huh?

14:33.734 --> 14:35.133
Yeah.

14:35.133 --> 14:38.234
You try and do a good thing,
you try and be a decent citizen.

14:40.834 --> 14:43.033
Hi. I'm, uh, Charlie.

14:43.033 --> 14:44.667
Only businessman in town

14:44.667 --> 14:46.367
that treats me
like a respectable man.

14:46.367 --> 14:47.901
You bet I'll shake your hand.

14:49.767 --> 14:53.033
So, uh...

14:53.033 --> 14:54.601
I take it
you're having a rough time.

14:54.601 --> 14:55.734
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

14:55.734 --> 14:57.033
Yeah. So are the Bosnians.

14:57.033 --> 14:59.234
So are the Kurds.
Everybody's got it rough.

14:59.234 --> 15:01.634
Who's Pete Terry to complain?

15:01.634 --> 15:05.200
What right does Pete Terry
have to a better life?

15:06.534 --> 15:09.133
Hey, you know what? Every right.

15:09.133 --> 15:11.868
You don't know that.

15:11.868 --> 15:14.067
For all you know,
I could be a felon.

15:14.067 --> 15:15.767
For all you know,
I coulda sold drugs

15:15.767 --> 15:18.367
to make cash
after I got laid off.

15:18.367 --> 15:21.267
Is that true? Did you do that?

15:22.534 --> 15:24.334
Ten years with
a pharmaceutical concern.

15:24.334 --> 15:26.334
You think you're secure.
Then bam, "See you."

15:26.334 --> 15:28.234
Four months severance.

15:28.234 --> 15:30.501
Four months later, the dealer's
the only one hiring.

15:30.501 --> 15:31.968
Bam, arrested.

15:31.968 --> 15:33.501
Bam, convicted.

15:33.501 --> 15:35.901
Two and a half years.

15:35.901 --> 15:37.200
Well, now I'm out,

15:37.200 --> 15:39.300
but who's gonna hire me?

15:39.300 --> 15:41.133
I bet lots of people would.

15:41.133 --> 15:42.801
I mean, you did your time.

15:42.801 --> 15:44.968
It doesn't matter.

15:44.968 --> 15:47.634
It's a one-strike game
we're playing here, Charlie.

15:47.634 --> 15:49.701
I swung, I missed.

15:52.033 --> 15:53.567
[SIGHS]

15:53.567 --> 15:56.701
CLAUDIA:
You sure do take your time
unwrapping things.

15:56.701 --> 15:58.534
No, it's--
It's done so beautifully.

15:58.534 --> 16:00.534
I don't wanna
ruin your work.

16:00.534 --> 16:01.968
Oh, no, no, no.
I didn't do it.

16:01.968 --> 16:04.167
The-- The guy
at the store did.

16:04.167 --> 16:06.801
Are you kidding?
That costs a fortune.

16:06.801 --> 16:08.267
No.

16:08.267 --> 16:09.567
No, no, no.
See, it was, uh--

16:09.567 --> 16:10.701
It was free.

16:14.534 --> 16:17.200
You got me this.

16:19.100 --> 16:22.033
Um, y-y-y-yeah.

16:22.033 --> 16:23.934
But--

16:23.934 --> 16:26.567
How did you know
I collect these?

16:30.901 --> 16:32.601
I got the epoxy
for you.

16:36.234 --> 16:37.434
They had two.

16:37.434 --> 16:39.133
I tried calling,
but your phone was busy

16:39.133 --> 16:42.000
for, like, forever,
so I just took a guess.

16:42.000 --> 16:43.334
She's not coming.

16:45.300 --> 16:46.634
What?

16:46.634 --> 16:47.701
She's not coming.

16:47.701 --> 16:49.901
A big snowstorm
on the east coast

16:49.901 --> 16:51.000
shut down the airports.

16:51.000 --> 16:53.334
That's why I was on the phone.

16:53.334 --> 16:55.167
Well, it has to be better
by tomorrow

16:55.167 --> 16:56.501
or the next day, right?

16:56.501 --> 17:00.067
Oh, she was only gonna
be here for three days.

17:00.067 --> 17:02.200
Her mom's taking her

17:02.200 --> 17:04.200
to the Caribbean
right after Christmas.

17:04.200 --> 17:06.267
Oh.

17:06.267 --> 17:09.233
Eh, so I'll see her
in the spring.

17:09.233 --> 17:10.601
It's only a few months.

17:14.032 --> 17:15.733
You know what?

17:15.733 --> 17:17.867
I'm still not doing anything.

17:17.867 --> 17:19.701
Why don't--? Why don't we
do something...

17:19.701 --> 17:20.701
tomorrow?

17:20.701 --> 17:21.767
Like, I don't know,

17:21.767 --> 17:23.233
go see a hockey game
or something?

17:23.233 --> 17:25.867
Ah, it's okay, Bailey. I know
you got stuff you wanna do.

17:25.867 --> 17:27.867
Yeah. I wanna go to a game.

17:28.901 --> 17:30.300
I think the Sharks
are playing.

17:30.300 --> 17:32.801
There's probably
some seats left.

17:32.801 --> 17:33.968
What do you say?

17:36.300 --> 17:38.267
What time is face-off?

17:38.267 --> 17:41.000
CHARLIE:
You like 'em?

17:41.000 --> 17:42.400
Sure.

17:42.400 --> 17:44.000
Whoo. They're thick.

17:44.000 --> 17:46.000
Figured you were, uh, a 34,
is that about right?

17:46.000 --> 17:49.467
Well, it depends on
how they fit, waist or hips.

17:49.467 --> 17:52.167
I have wider hips 'cause I took
female hormones when I was a kid

17:52.167 --> 17:54.801
as an experiment,
a medical experiment.

17:54.801 --> 17:56.701
It's a study
in hormonal inversion.

17:56.701 --> 17:58.734
I also grabbed you
a couple shirts

17:58.734 --> 18:00.834
so that when you
go on an interview,

18:00.834 --> 18:03.434
you'll look like somebody
who has his act together.

18:03.434 --> 18:05.300
I don't have
any interview.

18:05.300 --> 18:06.601
Aha.

18:06.601 --> 18:07.934
Yet.

18:09.267 --> 18:11.000
Classifieds.

18:11.000 --> 18:12.634
We're gonna sit here,

18:12.634 --> 18:14.534
figure out which ones
you should go up for.

18:16.334 --> 18:18.534
Nobody's gonna
give me a job.

18:18.534 --> 18:19.801
Hey, listen, you walk in there

18:19.801 --> 18:21.501
dressed right
with a positive attitude

18:21.501 --> 18:23.968
and they're gonna see someone
who wants to make a new start.

18:23.968 --> 18:26.033
And they're gonna
wanna help you.

18:26.033 --> 18:28.167
People do get second chances.

18:29.434 --> 18:31.334
So...

18:33.200 --> 18:34.367
Hey, Jake.

18:34.367 --> 18:35.634
Oh, hi.

18:35.634 --> 18:38.334
I, uh, got you a present.

18:38.334 --> 18:41.901
Oh, no. No present
before the big day.

18:41.901 --> 18:44.100
No. I-it's not
a Christmas present.

18:45.601 --> 18:46.868
Oh.

18:48.701 --> 18:51.300
It's not a Christmas
present, huh?

18:51.300 --> 18:54.033
Here,
just press the top.

18:55.934 --> 18:58.000
RECORDED VOICE:
 <i>Twelve a.m.</i>

18:59.834 --> 19:01.000
I saw you having trouble

19:01.000 --> 19:03.567
finding your watch
this morning.

19:05.834 --> 19:07.567
I wasn't having trouble.

19:07.567 --> 19:10.067
That and the book.

19:10.067 --> 19:13.400
You're having trouble
seeing, huh?

19:13.400 --> 19:15.434
No. I'm okay.

19:17.000 --> 19:19.567
Well, I'm an old man.

19:19.567 --> 19:21.100
I've got old eyes.

19:21.100 --> 19:22.868
I'm gonna take you
to a doctor.

19:22.868 --> 19:24.133
I have a doctor.

19:24.133 --> 19:25.934
He's a very good doctor.

19:25.934 --> 19:27.567
I'm okay.

19:27.567 --> 19:28.767
This is...

19:28.767 --> 19:32.000
what they call
a degenerative thing.

19:32.000 --> 19:33.334
That's the term.

19:34.400 --> 19:36.734
De...generative?

19:36.734 --> 19:38.767
Y-you mean,
you're going blind?

19:40.801 --> 19:42.901
Yes, I will be going blind.

19:45.901 --> 19:47.534
Oh.

19:47.534 --> 19:48.834
God, I'm, uh...

19:49.834 --> 19:51.601
I'm sorry.

19:51.601 --> 19:53.467
I'm okay now.

19:53.467 --> 19:56.133
Hey, I can manage the stairs.

19:57.367 --> 19:59.934
I travel, planes, buses.

19:59.934 --> 20:01.501
There's no problem
at all.

20:03.501 --> 20:04.634
Now, listen.

20:06.734 --> 20:09.100
I don't want you to tell
the other kids about this thing.

20:09.100 --> 20:11.767
I don't want them
treating me like an invalid.

20:13.167 --> 20:14.767
Okay.

20:14.767 --> 20:16.667
And don't you be sad.

20:17.834 --> 20:19.734
I've lived a long time.

20:19.734 --> 20:21.467
And I've seen, uh,

20:21.467 --> 20:23.667
so many beautiful things

20:23.667 --> 20:24.801
in this life.

20:24.801 --> 20:28.133
And I have them
all filed away,

20:28.133 --> 20:29.400
alphabetically.

20:31.100 --> 20:33.868
And now I have a new one

20:33.868 --> 20:35.634
u-under C.

20:37.334 --> 20:38.634
Christmas

20:38.634 --> 20:40.300
with my grandchildren.

20:41.968 --> 20:43.901
[***]

20:56.334 --> 20:57.634
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

20:57.634 --> 20:58.834
He's going blind?

20:58.834 --> 21:00.000
Yes.

21:00.000 --> 21:02.067
How do you even know this?

21:02.067 --> 21:03.701
Have you seen him?

21:03.701 --> 21:05.300
God, Bailey,
have you even listened

21:05.300 --> 21:06.868
to your messages lately?

21:06.868 --> 21:08.734
He's here.
He's staying with us.

21:10.067 --> 21:11.567
[SIGHS]

21:11.567 --> 21:13.400
I'm sorry. I just--

21:13.400 --> 21:15.434
I've had some other
stuff going on.

21:15.434 --> 21:17.234
But, okay.

21:17.234 --> 21:19.834
Okay, I'll stop by,
and I'll say hi.

21:19.834 --> 21:21.400
Oh, great.

21:21.400 --> 21:23.200
Another one of your
drive-bys.

21:23.200 --> 21:25.133
Well, what do you want from me?

21:26.267 --> 21:28.033
I want...

21:28.033 --> 21:30.067
Look, I'm all alone
in this, okay?

21:30.067 --> 21:31.434
I can't talk to Claudia.

21:31.434 --> 21:33.400
And Charlie is at work
all the time, so--

21:33.400 --> 21:36.501
So I want you to come home
for Christmas.

21:36.501 --> 21:38.267
I'm not doing Christmas
this year.

21:38.267 --> 21:39.767
Get over yourself,
Bailey.

21:39.767 --> 21:41.601
Our grandfather is going blind.

21:41.601 --> 21:43.934
How hard can it be
to spend a little time with him?

21:43.934 --> 21:46.434
I'm not saying it's hard.
I'm just--

21:46.434 --> 21:48.901
I'm busy, actually.

21:48.901 --> 21:50.701
I happen to have someplace else
I have to be.

21:53.567 --> 21:54.901
Okay, Bailey, look,

21:54.901 --> 21:57.367
I know you really wanna
check out right now.

21:57.367 --> 22:00.000
But Jake is family.
So whatever else you have to do,

22:00.000 --> 22:02.667
I think you should cancel it
because this is more important.

22:05.701 --> 22:07.067
[DOOR OPENS]

22:09.901 --> 22:12.701
You're late.
Late for what?

22:12.701 --> 22:15.133
I'm just dropping by to see,
uh, if you have any food

22:15.133 --> 22:16.934
you want me to
take back to the shelter.

22:16.934 --> 22:18.667
Heh. Yeah. Sure.

22:18.667 --> 22:21.300
I'm sorry, Xander, I--
I thought you were Pete.

22:21.300 --> 22:23.033
Pete Terry?

22:23.033 --> 22:24.934
Yeah. I'm, uh,

22:24.934 --> 22:26.067
helping him get a job.

22:26.067 --> 22:28.167
Some people already called
to set up interviews.

22:28.167 --> 22:30.934
Are you sure
that's such a good idea?

22:30.934 --> 22:33.033
I mean, considering his history.

22:33.033 --> 22:35.801
Hey, the guy only
made one mistake.

22:35.801 --> 22:37.367
People can change.

22:37.367 --> 22:39.267
They can realize
where they went wrong

22:39.267 --> 22:40.701
and turn their lives around.

22:40.701 --> 22:42.834
Yeah. Sure, Charlie.
No argument.

22:42.834 --> 22:44.934
It's just that, uh,
it's different

22:44.934 --> 22:47.000
when you're talking about
a schizophrenic.

22:47.000 --> 22:48.300
A what?

22:48.300 --> 22:49.667
Pete's a schizophrenic.

22:49.667 --> 22:51.367
The state gives him medication,

22:51.367 --> 22:52.868
which he usually sells.

22:52.868 --> 22:54.501
But when he's off it,

22:54.501 --> 22:57.701
reality's kinda nebulous.

22:58.200 --> 23:00.133
Pete.

23:00.133 --> 23:01.334
Um, where--?

23:01.334 --> 23:02.601
Where are
the clothes we got?

23:02.601 --> 23:04.534
I can't wear 'em now.

23:04.534 --> 23:07.067
They make me too conspicuous.
They're in a safe place.

23:07.067 --> 23:09.634
In a little while,
I'll get 'em. I'll come to work.

23:09.634 --> 23:12.167
But not now.
They make me too conspicuous.

23:20.200 --> 23:21.367
Stuart.

23:21.367 --> 23:22.834
It's a thank-you note.

23:22.834 --> 23:25.033
You couldn't mail it?
What? This time of year?

23:25.033 --> 23:27.300
We'd be lucky if you
got it by New Year's.

23:27.300 --> 23:29.801
Wanna know what it says?
I--

23:29.801 --> 23:33.200
"Dear Claudia, thank you
for the thoughtful gift.

23:33.200 --> 23:36.167
"I am moved by the care
you took in selecting it.

23:36.167 --> 23:38.501
"Looking forward
to our future

23:38.501 --> 23:39.901
"with anticipation.

23:39.901 --> 23:42.534
"I remain yours truly,

23:42.534 --> 23:44.200
Stuart."

23:44.200 --> 23:46.601
Look, Stuart,

23:46.601 --> 23:48.534
you're a nice guy,

23:48.534 --> 23:53.133
but there isn't going to be
any future for us.

23:53.133 --> 23:55.667
I mean,
I-I don't like you like that.

23:57.300 --> 23:58.501
But that gift...

23:58.501 --> 24:00.100
Was supposed to be impersonal.

24:00.100 --> 24:01.701
I mean, how was I supposed
to know that

24:01.701 --> 24:03.033
that would mean something?

24:03.033 --> 24:06.133
I mean, what kind of a person
collects those things?

24:06.133 --> 24:07.434
My kind.

24:07.434 --> 24:08.667
Oh, I-I'm-- I'm sorry.

24:08.667 --> 24:10.434
Th-that came out wrong.
I didn't mean--

24:10.434 --> 24:12.367
And here I thought
you were this nice person.

24:12.367 --> 24:13.934
I am nice.
No, you're not.

24:13.934 --> 24:16.133
A nice person
doesn't lead people on

24:16.133 --> 24:18.200
and then squash their hearts
like a bug.

24:20.000 --> 24:21.801
I never led you on.

24:21.801 --> 24:22.834
Oh, right.

24:22.834 --> 24:24.801
Like I just imagined
the whole thing.

24:26.467 --> 24:27.501
[SCOFFS]

24:27.501 --> 24:29.267
[DOOR SLAMS]

24:30.167 --> 24:31.434
RUSS:
Hey, come on in.

24:31.434 --> 24:33.334
I'm just nuking up
a Hungry-Man dinner here.

24:33.334 --> 24:34.467
Thanks.

24:34.467 --> 24:36.267
I-I got another one
I could heat up for you.

24:36.267 --> 24:37.701
It only takes seven minutes.

24:37.701 --> 24:40.501
We'll still have plenty of time
to make it to the stadium.

24:40.501 --> 24:42.067
Yeah, um,

24:42.067 --> 24:44.200
about that.

24:44.200 --> 24:45.267
I can't go.

24:45.267 --> 24:47.634
I'm actually
heading home.

24:47.634 --> 24:48.968
Home?

24:48.968 --> 24:51.601
You mean, family home?
Yeah.

24:51.601 --> 24:53.100
It turns out

24:53.100 --> 24:54.567
there's some stuff
going on there

24:54.567 --> 24:56.367
that I should...

24:56.367 --> 24:58.234
Anyway.

24:58.234 --> 24:59.667
I said I'd go.

25:00.734 --> 25:02.334
Oh, sure. I understand. That's--

25:02.334 --> 25:04.467
But I feel really bad
about this.

25:04.467 --> 25:06.067
You know, I mean,

25:06.067 --> 25:07.934
we said we were gonna do this.

25:07.934 --> 25:08.934
Oh, no, no.

25:08.934 --> 25:10.334
No sweat.

25:10.334 --> 25:12.601
It's Christmas Eve. You should
be with your family.

25:12.601 --> 25:14.567
[MICROWAVE BEEPING]

25:14.567 --> 25:16.000
Um, that's my dinner.
I gotta...

25:16.000 --> 25:17.734
[CHUCKLES]

25:17.734 --> 25:19.934
[MICROWAVE DOOR OPENS]

25:19.934 --> 25:21.634
Listen, you tell
your family I wish them

25:21.634 --> 25:23.534
a very Merry Christmas,
huh?

25:28.434 --> 25:31.267
JAKE:
He's gonna come sliding
right down there

25:31.267 --> 25:34.000
with a big bag of presents
to leave in the house.

25:34.000 --> 25:35.000
No.

25:35.000 --> 25:36.200
What do you mean, "no"?

25:36.200 --> 25:38.601
O-oh, yes, he will.

25:38.601 --> 25:40.634
You wait and see
and tomorrow,

25:40.634 --> 25:43.934
all these stockings will be
full of presents left by him.

25:43.934 --> 25:45.501
BAILEY:
Okay.

25:45.501 --> 25:48.367
We got moo shu.
We got kung pao.

25:48.367 --> 25:50.934
We got potstickers.

25:50.934 --> 25:53.400
Traditional
Christmas Eve dinner.

25:53.400 --> 25:55.701
[LAUGHTER]
Around here it is.

25:58.167 --> 26:01.234
Uh, Julia, you didn't need
to do that.

26:01.234 --> 26:03.534
Yes, I did.

26:03.534 --> 26:05.667
'Cause a stocking's
what you hang at Christmas

26:05.667 --> 26:07.334
to say,
"This is where I belong."

26:07.334 --> 26:09.601
And you belong here.

26:09.601 --> 26:10.968
Oh, no, kids.

26:10.968 --> 26:12.133
I don't belong here.

26:12.133 --> 26:15.300
I just came by
to leave a few presents

26:15.300 --> 26:16.968
and spend a little time
with you,

26:16.968 --> 26:18.767
but, um...

26:18.767 --> 26:20.234
But, uh, this is, uh--

26:20.234 --> 26:22.734
This is-- This is your home,
not mine.

26:22.734 --> 26:24.901
Well, I-I guess
what we're saying

26:24.901 --> 26:26.834
is we like having you around
this time of year.

26:26.834 --> 26:28.501
And that it would
be nice

26:28.501 --> 26:30.300
if you were here
next Christmas too.

26:30.300 --> 26:31.334
Right, Bay?

26:31.334 --> 26:32.701
BAILEY:
Yeah.

26:32.701 --> 26:34.167
That would be...

26:34.167 --> 26:35.534
That would be good.

26:35.534 --> 26:37.400
CLAUDIA:
And the one after that.

26:37.400 --> 26:39.734
We'll do it just like this,
every single year.

26:40.434 --> 26:41.767
No matter what.

26:48.334 --> 26:49.767
Charlie?

26:51.567 --> 26:53.501
When did you get back
from the restaurant?

26:55.033 --> 26:57.067
Um...

26:57.067 --> 26:59.701
half an hour ago, maybe.

27:01.100 --> 27:03.868
So, um, what was going on
down there?

27:03.868 --> 27:06.100
Lots of busy holiday stuff?

27:07.467 --> 27:08.868
I don't know.

27:08.868 --> 27:10.434
What do you mean?

27:11.567 --> 27:13.467
You were-- You were there.

27:14.901 --> 27:16.834
Yeah.

27:16.834 --> 27:18.501
I just don't know
what's going on.

27:21.000 --> 27:23.701
We're doing the tree downstairs.

27:23.701 --> 27:25.968
Bay was gonna do the lights,

27:25.968 --> 27:27.367
but I told him not to

27:27.367 --> 27:29.334
'cause I know
you love to do them.

27:31.267 --> 27:32.667
It's okay. He can.

27:32.667 --> 27:34.000
No.

27:34.000 --> 27:35.300
It's your job.

27:36.501 --> 27:37.767
And if someone else does it,

27:37.767 --> 27:39.667
it'd be like saying

27:39.667 --> 27:41.434
that you're not here.

27:44.434 --> 27:46.801
And you are.

27:48.000 --> 27:49.467
Right?

27:49.467 --> 27:51.567
Yeah, Claud,

27:51.567 --> 27:53.300
I'm here.

27:53.300 --> 27:55.501
So come downstairs.

27:57.567 --> 27:59.834
Come downstairs
and do the lights.

28:05.300 --> 28:07.267
[***]

28:39.501 --> 28:41.801
JAKE:
The address

28:41.801 --> 28:43.934
is 33-24 Broadway.

28:44.968 --> 28:46.934
Listen, t-tell your driver

28:46.934 --> 28:49.634
not to honk, please.

28:49.634 --> 28:51.501
I-I'll be waiting for him.

28:51.501 --> 28:52.667
Thanks.

28:55.334 --> 28:57.434
Man.

28:57.434 --> 28:58.767
[CHUCKLES]

28:58.767 --> 29:01.167
Thought I had
bad staying power, but you...

29:01.167 --> 29:03.801
I'm not running away
from anything, Charlie.

29:03.801 --> 29:05.367
Right.

29:05.367 --> 29:08.367
Okay. That's what I'll tell
Claudia in the morning.

29:08.367 --> 29:10.234
See you, Jake. It's been real.

29:10.234 --> 29:11.534
Charlie, wait a minute.

29:15.701 --> 29:18.067
I've got an appointment

29:18.067 --> 29:19.767
that I must keep.

29:21.934 --> 29:24.400
I never intended staying.

29:24.400 --> 29:27.000
I've stayed

29:27.000 --> 29:29.200
two days too long already,

29:29.200 --> 29:30.834
and-- And now I've simply
gotta leave.

29:32.400 --> 29:34.501
What kind of appointment
could you possibly have

29:34.501 --> 29:36.067
on Christmas morning?

29:37.901 --> 29:40.801
It's an appointment
for chemotherapy.

29:42.767 --> 29:44.234
What?

29:45.267 --> 29:47.133
Treatment for cancer.

29:52.167 --> 29:54.033
Jake, God, um...

29:57.133 --> 29:59.434
I'm sorry.
God, what I just said--

29:59.434 --> 30:01.467
Don't let it worry you.

30:01.467 --> 30:03.467
You were only trying
to stick up for the kids.

30:03.467 --> 30:05.300
You were doing just fine.

30:05.300 --> 30:07.067
Let us help.

30:07.067 --> 30:08.801
We're-- We're family.

30:08.801 --> 30:10.667
I don't wanna
play that card.

30:11.934 --> 30:14.167
If I'd been around

30:14.167 --> 30:15.834
all the time

30:15.834 --> 30:17.701
and had really been
a member of the family,

30:17.701 --> 30:19.334
it'd be a different story but--

30:19.334 --> 30:22.968
That's not the way
it works, Jake.

30:27.467 --> 30:29.701
Claudia was just...

30:29.701 --> 30:31.567
so excited to have you here.

30:31.567 --> 30:34.033
Oh, I think she can handle it.

30:34.033 --> 30:37.667
I know she can handle it...

30:37.667 --> 30:40.501
better than losing me
little by little.

30:42.133 --> 30:44.033
Don't you think so?

30:47.067 --> 30:49.634
Well, that's the answer.

30:51.834 --> 30:54.501
Now, don't feel bad about this.

30:57.267 --> 30:59.234
But listen, maybe you think

30:59.234 --> 31:02.334
that I don't love those kids.

31:02.334 --> 31:04.868
I'm gonna tell you, I do.

31:04.868 --> 31:06.601
I love them.

31:07.634 --> 31:09.334
And I love you.

31:13.968 --> 31:16.300
I love you all.

31:16.300 --> 31:18.234
[***]

31:38.167 --> 31:40.133
Julia, is this from you?

31:40.133 --> 31:41.567
JULIA:
Hm? What?

31:41.567 --> 31:43.334
Santa Claus?

31:45.033 --> 31:46.601
Oh.

31:54.133 --> 31:55.767
"This belonged to my mother,

31:55.767 --> 31:57.300
"your great-grandmother.

31:57.300 --> 31:59.901
"She was a great music lover
and would be happy to know

31:59.901 --> 32:02.200
"it was being worn
by her great-granddaughter,

32:02.200 --> 32:03.701
"the violinist.

32:03.701 --> 32:05.000
"Merry Christmas.

32:07.501 --> 32:08.701
Love, Grandpa."

32:10.567 --> 32:13.467
Ungh. Why is there no coffee
in the machine?

32:13.467 --> 32:15.300
We ran out. Bailey went
to get some, like,

32:15.300 --> 32:18.434
six hours ago. Where's he
buying it, Columbia?

32:18.434 --> 32:20.100
What'd you get?
Another candy cane.

32:20.100 --> 32:21.934
Another candy cane?

32:21.934 --> 32:23.434
[LAUGHS]

32:23.434 --> 32:25.000
I'm gonna go wake him up.

32:26.200 --> 32:27.434
Wait.

32:27.434 --> 32:28.834
I just said
he went to get coffee.

32:28.834 --> 32:30.033
Not Bailey. Grandpa.

32:30.033 --> 32:31.701
I mean, I'm sure
he doesn't wanna sleep

32:31.701 --> 32:33.968
throughout the whole day.
No, Claud, wait. Hang on.

32:36.267 --> 32:37.501
Um, he's not there.

32:37.501 --> 32:39.133
What? Well, where is he?

32:39.133 --> 32:40.567
He's, uh...

32:40.567 --> 32:41.634
He had to go,

32:41.634 --> 32:43.767
early this morning.

32:43.767 --> 32:45.033
Wait, he left?
Candy cane.

32:45.033 --> 32:46.968
Yeah. He didn't want to, though.

32:46.968 --> 32:48.133
Um, he--

32:48.133 --> 32:49.400
Last night he--

32:49.400 --> 32:51.400
I guess he started thinking
about his daughter.

32:51.400 --> 32:54.000
And he thought that maybe since
he was here on Christmas Eve,

32:54.000 --> 32:55.834
he should be there
on Christmas Day.

32:55.834 --> 32:57.767
But...

32:58.634 --> 33:00.701
why didn't he say anything?

33:00.701 --> 33:02.567
Like I said, it--

33:02.567 --> 33:04.968
It didn't occur to him
until late last night.

33:04.968 --> 33:06.167
So...

33:06.167 --> 33:07.767
So he just...

33:09.801 --> 33:11.100
walked away?

33:14.067 --> 33:16.968
After everything we did for him.

33:16.968 --> 33:18.701
I'm sure he didn't want to,
Claud. Uh--

33:21.133 --> 33:22.234
[DOOR OPENS]

33:22.234 --> 33:24.100
See, my sisters
always bitch about me

33:24.100 --> 33:26.434
watching the game
on Christmas.

33:26.434 --> 33:29.067
But with you here, that's like
part of your job, right?

33:29.067 --> 33:31.634
I mean, you have to watch.
Leave me out of it, huh?

33:31.634 --> 33:34.133
Charlie, Julia, Owen,

33:34.133 --> 33:36.567
this is Russ Petrocelli,
my coach.

33:36.567 --> 33:37.968
RUSS: Hi.
BAILEY: He's gonna be

33:37.968 --> 33:40.100
hanging out with us today.
Hey.

33:40.100 --> 33:41.267
If it's all right with you.

33:41.267 --> 33:42.934
Well, can you cook?

33:42.934 --> 33:44.868
I can peel and chop things.

33:44.868 --> 33:47.133
Good enough. Follow me.

33:50.534 --> 33:52.267
Only until kickoff.

34:02.000 --> 34:04.934
What do you want now, Stuart?

34:04.934 --> 34:07.167
Um, well, I'm here to apologize.

34:07.167 --> 34:09.833
Look, y-y-y-you didn't
lead me on.

34:09.833 --> 34:11.199
And you're not a mean person.

34:11.199 --> 34:13.434
I only said those things
because I was ashamed.

34:13.434 --> 34:16.167
And now even more ashamed
because I said those things,

34:16.167 --> 34:18.434
and I'm-- I'm really sorry,
and I feel really stupid,

34:18.434 --> 34:20.434
and I just think that we--
Enough, Stuart.

34:21.667 --> 34:23.033
Apology accepted.

34:23.734 --> 34:25.801
Really?

34:25.801 --> 34:27.667
Phew.

34:27.667 --> 34:29.833
Well, okay.

34:30.900 --> 34:32.734
So we can be friends again?

34:32.734 --> 34:34.300
Yeah.

34:34.300 --> 34:35.900
Why not?

34:35.900 --> 34:37.567
Great.

34:41.833 --> 34:42.801
[EXHALES]

34:46.400 --> 34:48.601
You know, I--
I couldn't help noticing

34:48.601 --> 34:51.634
all the cooking going on
in the kitchen.

34:51.634 --> 34:52.868
Yeah, you know.

34:52.868 --> 34:55.400
Christmas dinner
is kind of a big thing.

34:55.400 --> 34:57.167
Turkey, hot cross buns.

34:57.167 --> 34:58.434
Stuff like that.

34:58.434 --> 35:01.033
Really? How interesting,

35:01.033 --> 35:04.501
uh, y-you know, culturally.

35:07.567 --> 35:09.667
Hey, Stuart.

35:09.667 --> 35:11.300
I have an idea.

35:12.567 --> 35:14.267
Why don't you stay?

35:14.267 --> 35:16.901
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

35:16.901 --> 35:19.334
[FRIDGE DOOR OPENS,
BOTTLES CLINKING]

35:19.334 --> 35:22.200
Is it halftime?
No.

35:22.200 --> 35:25.267
Called time out to cart some guy
with a concussion off the field.

35:27.000 --> 35:28.968
I like your coach.

35:28.968 --> 35:31.501
Even if he lied
about being able to chop.

35:34.501 --> 35:37.100
That was a nice thing you did

35:37.100 --> 35:38.467
asking him here.

35:38.467 --> 35:40.834
I only did it
'cause I had to.

35:40.834 --> 35:42.133
That's not true.

35:42.133 --> 35:43.868
You did it
'cause you're a good guy.

35:43.868 --> 35:45.601
Okay.

35:45.601 --> 35:47.467
Look, let's be honest here,
Jule, okay?

35:47.467 --> 35:49.467
'Cause that's true,
and you know it's not true.

35:49.467 --> 35:51.200
And in case you forgot
why it's not true,

35:51.200 --> 35:54.300
why don't you give Sarah a call?
I'm sure she'll remind you.

35:54.300 --> 35:55.701
[CLANGING]

35:55.701 --> 35:57.234
Where the hell
is the bottle opener?

36:02.367 --> 36:04.701
You know what, Bay?

36:04.701 --> 36:05.934
I really think

36:05.934 --> 36:07.934
that if you're gonna
punish yourself this hard

36:07.934 --> 36:09.801
for the bad stuff you do,
you should at least

36:09.801 --> 36:13.434
give yourself some credit
for the good things.

36:13.434 --> 36:15.400
I mean, yeah,
you messed up with Sarah,

36:15.400 --> 36:17.067
but like it or not,

36:17.067 --> 36:18.634
you're still the kind of guy

36:18.634 --> 36:21.033
who's not gonna let someone
spend Christmas alone,

36:21.033 --> 36:22.400
and that's...

36:23.901 --> 36:25.067
That's what?

36:27.000 --> 36:28.367
I don't know.

36:28.367 --> 36:30.434
But it's gotta be something.

36:38.000 --> 36:40.234
Oh, I didn't know
you were out here.

36:40.234 --> 36:42.667
I just--
It's okay. Hey.

36:42.667 --> 36:43.868
What are you doing?

36:43.868 --> 36:46.667
Just looking for someplace

36:46.667 --> 36:49.667
where no one else is,
I guess.

36:49.667 --> 36:51.334
How come?

36:52.400 --> 36:53.634
I don't know.

37:01.367 --> 37:03.968
It doesn't really feel
like Christmas in there.

37:06.734 --> 37:08.968
No one wants to be here,

37:09.601 --> 37:11.300
except Stuart.

37:11.300 --> 37:14.734
It's not that I don't
wanna be here, Claud.

37:14.734 --> 37:17.634
Right.

37:17.634 --> 37:20.100
You're probably
just sitting there thinking

37:20.100 --> 37:22.000
what your life would be like

37:22.000 --> 37:24.601
if you didn't have to
take care of me and Owen.

37:29.300 --> 37:30.801
[MOUTHED SPEECH]

37:30.801 --> 37:32.567
You don't really
think that, do you?

37:32.567 --> 37:34.534
I don't know.

37:38.801 --> 37:39.934
Maybe.

37:39.934 --> 37:42.234
[SIGHS]

37:42.234 --> 37:45.100
I like taking care of you,
Claudia.

37:45.100 --> 37:47.501
I like dropping you off
at school.

37:47.501 --> 37:49.901
I like hearing about what guy
you have a crush on.

37:49.901 --> 37:52.167
I like taking you
to the dentist.

37:52.167 --> 37:55.300
I like it all. I wouldn't trade
that for anything in the world.

37:55.300 --> 37:57.133
Yeah.

37:58.767 --> 38:00.634
But it doesn't
make you happy.

38:02.067 --> 38:03.334
It's just...

38:05.367 --> 38:07.734
not quite enough.

38:07.734 --> 38:08.834
You know?

38:11.734 --> 38:14.734
I mean, I love you.

38:14.734 --> 38:17.801
But I guess I want a little more
out of life too.

38:21.067 --> 38:22.367
And that's hard

38:22.367 --> 38:25.801
because I was so close
to having that.

38:25.801 --> 38:28.701
Marrying Kirsten
would have been much more.

38:28.701 --> 38:30.567
Much more.

38:30.567 --> 38:33.100
And it's not
like I wanna replace her,

38:33.100 --> 38:34.901
'cause I know
that I'm never gonna have her

38:34.901 --> 38:36.734
or anything like her again.

38:38.033 --> 38:40.067
I just...

38:40.067 --> 38:42.734
wouldn't mind something.

38:44.534 --> 38:46.133
It doesn't even
have to be a big thing,

38:46.133 --> 38:47.834
you know?

38:47.834 --> 38:50.167
Just something small. Heh.

38:50.167 --> 38:51.634
For me.

38:53.300 --> 38:55.701
[***]

38:57.968 --> 38:59.567
Looks nice, Julia.

38:59.567 --> 39:01.801
Yeah, it does,
doesn't it?

39:03.000 --> 39:04.734
Dinner's ready!

39:07.834 --> 39:08.901
[SIGHS]

39:08.901 --> 39:10.634
Oh, um,
we're short a chair,

39:10.634 --> 39:12.300
so someone has to
take the piano stool.

39:12.300 --> 39:13.501
Oh, I will.

39:17.033 --> 39:18.834
CLAUDIA:
This looks great, Jule.

39:18.834 --> 39:22.200
Yeah, if we can sidestep
last year's salmonella incident.

39:22.200 --> 39:23.868
Salmonella?

39:23.868 --> 39:25.133
You had the flu.

39:25.133 --> 39:26.133
It was the flu.

39:27.434 --> 39:28.567
Right.

39:30.534 --> 39:31.901
Well, should we,

39:31.901 --> 39:34.100
I don't know,
say a blessing or something?

39:35.501 --> 39:36.767
We could.

39:40.100 --> 39:41.334
[CLEARS THROAT]

39:46.634 --> 39:50.267
[HUMS "THE LITTLE DRUMMER BOY"]

39:53.234 --> 39:54.300
Amen.

39:54.300 --> 39:55.801
Amen.
Amen.

39:55.801 --> 39:56.868
Amen.

39:56.868 --> 39:58.200
[LAUGHS]

39:58.200 --> 40:00.267
RUSS:
That was very good.

40:00.267 --> 40:02.200
[CHATTERING, DOORBELL RINGS]

40:03.534 --> 40:05.968
Want some of this, O?

40:05.968 --> 40:07.901
[CHATTERING CONTINUES]

40:10.901 --> 40:12.767
Grace.
Charlie,

40:12.767 --> 40:15.400
I-I thought you were in Chicago.

40:15.400 --> 40:17.334
I was.

40:17.334 --> 40:20.033
But, uh, now I'm home.

40:21.334 --> 40:22.434
Alone?

40:22.434 --> 40:24.367
Yeah.

40:24.367 --> 40:26.200
Well, no. I mean,
my family's here,

40:26.200 --> 40:29.400
but, um--
But I'm alone, yeah.

40:29.400 --> 40:31.000
Oh.

40:31.000 --> 40:32.501
Well, I'm sorry.

40:34.334 --> 40:35.734
Well, I don't, uh--

40:35.734 --> 40:38.367
I don't wanna keep you.
I just wanted to bring this by.

40:38.367 --> 40:39.801
[LAUGHS]
It's cranberry bread.

40:39.801 --> 40:41.300
Merry Christmas.

40:41.300 --> 40:43.234
Oh, wow.

40:43.234 --> 40:45.567
Grace, thanks.
Oh, it's nothing.

40:45.567 --> 40:47.434
It's just something small.

40:50.868 --> 40:52.734
Listen, um, can you come in?

40:52.734 --> 40:54.300
We're just sitting down
to dinner.

40:54.300 --> 40:55.901
Oh, that's nice.

40:55.901 --> 40:57.334
But I've--
I've already eaten.

40:57.334 --> 40:59.634
That's okay.
I won't tell anybody.

40:59.634 --> 41:00.601
[CHUCKLES]

41:03.167 --> 41:06.100
[PLAYING "SILENT NIGHT"]

41:06.100 --> 41:07.701
What do you say
we give it a spin, huh?

41:07.701 --> 41:09.367
Here you go.
[DINGS]

41:09.367 --> 41:12.367
Woo, you wouldn't know where
those wrenches are, would you?

41:12.367 --> 41:14.868
Mrs. Reeves, hi. It's Bailey.

41:14.868 --> 41:16.801
Thanks. You too.

41:16.801 --> 41:18.033
Is Sarah there?

41:20.267 --> 41:22.567
Hi.

41:22.567 --> 41:24.901
I just wanted to wish you
a Merry Christmas.

41:26.133 --> 41:28.534
Thanks.

41:28.534 --> 41:30.367
I'm sorry I didn't call sooner.

41:30.367 --> 41:33.067
Um, things have been
kinda hectic around here.

41:34.567 --> 41:35.934
Yeah.

41:37.200 --> 41:39.834
Yeah. Not bad.

41:39.834 --> 41:41.300
How about you?

41:41.300 --> 41:43.200
How's everything
in Florida?

41:49.534 --> 41:52.434
You look so cute.

41:52.434 --> 41:54.734
Uh, actually, that's my dad
when he was little.

41:54.734 --> 41:57.334
Wow, you really take after him,
don't you?

41:57.334 --> 41:59.534
Maybe. I don't know.

41:59.534 --> 42:01.801
[OWEN IMITATING MOTOR]

42:05.067 --> 42:06.501
Who's that playing?

42:06.501 --> 42:08.067
Stuart.

42:08.067 --> 42:10.834
Really? For a first-timer, he's
really embracing the holiday.

42:10.834 --> 42:12.501
Hey, as long as
he's not embracing me,

42:12.501 --> 42:14.367
I'm not complaining.

42:14.367 --> 42:19.300
["HAVE YOURSELF A MERRY LITTLE
CHRISTMAS" PLAYING]

42:20.000 --> 42:21.934
[HUMMING]

42:28.234 --> 42:30.167
* Once again *

42:30.167 --> 42:32.434
* As in olden days *

42:32.434 --> 42:37.067
* Happy golden days of yore *

42:38.567 --> 42:40.133
BOTH:
* Faithful friends *

42:40.133 --> 42:42.567
* Who were dear to us *

42:42.567 --> 42:45.133
* <i>Will be near to us</i> *

42:45.133 --> 42:48.100
* <i>Once more</i> *

42:48.100 --> 42:50.033
* <i>Through the years</i> *

42:50.033 --> 42:53.534
* <i>We all will be together</i> *

42:53.534 --> 42:57.801
* <i>If the fates allow</i> *

42:57.801 --> 42:59.934
* <i>Until then</i> *

42:59.934 --> 43:04.267
* <i>We'll have to</i>
 <i>Muddle through somehow</i> *

43:07.434 --> 43:10.934
* And have yourself *

43:10.934 --> 43:17.567
* A merry little Christmas *

43:17.567 --> 43:22.300
 <i>* Now *</i>

